# Cloudflare Pages — HTTP response headers applied to every route.
#
# script-src is HASH-LOCKED: it lists 'sha256-...' of the exact MINIFIED bytes of
# the inline scripts Hugo emits (theme toggle, menu/top-link/reading-progress,
# code-copy) instead of 'unsafe-inline', so injected inline scripts are blocked.
# application/ld+json data blocks aren't script-src-governed (no hash needed), and
# there are no inline on*= event handlers (which hashes can't cover).
# MAINTENANCE: if you edit the inline reading-progress script in
# layouts/_partials/extend_head.html, OR bump HUGO_VERSION / the PaperMod submodule
# (either changes the minified bytes), these hashes go stale and that inline script
# gets blocked (theme toggle / reading bar / code-copy silently break). Regenerate
# with:  ~/Desktop/my_scripts/csp-hashes.sh  and paste the script-src tokens below.
#
# style-src KEEPS 'unsafe-inline' — the theme sets background images via inline
# style="background-image:url(...)" ATTRIBUTES (hero + site bg in list.html /
# extend_footer.html, and per-post featured-card covers). CSP hashes only cover
# <style> BLOCKS, never style="" attributes, and the URLs are per-post/dynamic, so
# hash- or nonce-locking style-src is not feasible without refactoring those out.
# (Removing 'unsafe-inline' here previously blanked the hero/site/featured-card
# backgrounds — the EFT hero image included.) Inline styles can't execute JS, so
# the residual risk is low.
#
# The <meta> CSP in layouts/_partials/extend_head.html is deliberately kept LOOSE
# ('unsafe-inline' for scripts too) as the local `hugo server` preview fallback
# (preview isn't minified, so the script hashes above wouldn't match it); in
# production both policies are enforced, so this stricter header still blocks
# injected inline scripts.
# NOTE: if you enable GoatCounter analytics later, also add
#   https://gc.zgo.at  to script-src   and   https://*.goatcounter.com  to img-src + connect-src.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://giscus.app 'sha256-bOIlT+8wbFz3AQtUEup46zzMyMh8mHc3lD1pmMtpJD8=' 'sha256-UBD9lfFHKxagKGHh9S8B2hytN1cmDsFK1Tl1uedsZ0Q=' 'sha256-5ilQRTfItUB+Etsk1onTDCqBA1OpUBIKfJhdMlZ61Co=' 'sha256-/cFFbEHjTjpj7DLefsC+h1yhrxRRebLCB86XtBuCtvw=' 'sha256-KHyHOOpYOFHylRCfkAjr3t7Ej1N6ByeUULOPShxcySo=' 'sha256-eyUVosQAviXm2qeOTG819D1n0kSst2gY8VmfgVsZlag='; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://giscus.app; font-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data: https://avatars.githubusercontent.com; connect-src 'self' https://giscus.app; frame-src https://giscus.app; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=()
  X-XSS-Protection: 0
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
